title: Beshear touts education plan ahead of lawmakers reconvening
description: Gov. Andy Beshear says Kentucky is lagging behind in the “competition for talent” to lead its classrooms. He renewed his push Monday for higher teacher pay as a way to overcome a shortage of educators. He's asking lawmakers to award…
author: By BRUCE SCHREINER - Associated Press

title: Kentucky Gov. Beshear makes another appeal for education spending
description: Democratic Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear spoke on the state's teacher shortage Monday, and is expected to push the state legislature to increase education funding.
author: Associated Press

title: Critics unleash on Democrat governor after disaster relief checks sent to random people: 'Gross mismanagement'
description: Democratic Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear faced sharp criticism this week after reports revealed his administration sent thousands of dollars in disaster relief funds to the wrong people.
author: Brandon Gillespie

title: Kentucky Gov. Beshear says expanded COVID Medicaid coverage soon to end
description: Democratic Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear announced Thursday that expanded Medicaid coverage which some residents qualified for during the COVID-19 pandemic would soon expire.
author: Associated Press

title: 'Border state problems' in Kentucky: Candidates attack Dem gov for state's response to fentanyl crisis
description: As Kentucky's gubernatorial race heats up, the drug crisis plaguing the state has taken center stage in the campaigns of each of the candidates hoping to unseat Democrat Gov. Andy Beshear.
author: Brandon Gillespie

title: Democrat Gov. Andy Beshear's tornado relief fund 'erroneously' sent unknown amounts of money to wrong people
description: A tornado relief fund started by Democratic Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear's administration "erroneously" sent out an unknown amount of money to people unaffected by the Dec. 2021 tornados.
author: Brandon Gillespie

title: Kentucky lawmakers press for juvenile justice changes
description: Kentucky lawmakers are pressing for changes in the juvenile justice system. The group of lawmakers wants someone outside of the system to address the growing problem of violence.
author: Associated Press

title: KY group creates 1st funding award to fight state’s opioid crisis
description: A Kentucky commission has created a $10 million pilot program to combat the state’s opioid epidemic. The program will offer health treatment for those struggling with drug use.
author: Associated Press

title: Eyes on 2024: GOP primary kicks off with Trump trips and sniping
description: Former President Trump visited New Hampshire and South Carolina this past weekend.
author: Ben Kamisar

title: Poll finds 71% of Americans believe country is on wrong track
description: 71% of Americans in a new NBC News poll say the country is headed in the wrong direction — the eighth time that level has been hit in the last nine NBC polls.
author: Chuck Todd
